{{Infobox book | name = Hardcore Zen: Punk Rock, Monster Movies, & the Truth about Reality | image = Hardcore Zen cover.jpg | caption = | author = [[Brad Warner]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = Elizabeth Lawrence | country = | language = English | series = | subject = [[Sōtō]] [[Zen|Zen Buddhism]] | publisher = [[Wisdom Publications]] | release_date = October 3, 2003 | english_release_date = | media_type = Print | pages = 224 | isbn = 0-86171-380-X | dewey= 294.3/927 21 | congress= BQ9288 .W37 2003 | oclc= 52348846 | preceded_by = | followed_by = [[Sit Down and Shut Up]] }}
'''''Hardcore Zen: Punk Rock, Monster Movies, & the Truth about Reality''''' is a book written by [[Brad Warner]], an author and ordained [[Zen]] priest. It was released in October [[2003 in literature|2003]] by [[Wisdom Publications]]. The work serves as both an autobiography and an introduction to [[Sōtō]] Zen philosophy.
==Reception== ''Hardcore Zen'' received mostly positive reviews. ''[[Publishers Weekly]]'' said of the book, "Entertaining, bold and refreshingly direct, this book is likely to change the way one experiences other books about Zen—and maybe even the way one experiences reality."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-86171-380-6 |title=Nonfiction review: Hardcore Zen |accessdate=May 17, 2012 |publisher=[[Publishers Weekly]] }}</ref> ''[[Tricycle: The Buddhist Review]]'' said "''Hardcore Zen'' is ''Be Here Now'' for now."<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.tricycle.com/reviews/books-brief-fall-2003 |title=Books in Brief |author=Joan Duncan Oliver | journal =[[Tricycle: The Buddhist Review]] | issue =2003 |accessdate=May 17, 2012 }}</ref>
