{{Infobox philosopher | region = [[Western philosophy]] | era = [[Contemporary philosophy]] | image = | caption = | name = Kevin Mulligan | birth_date = {{bda|1951|6|23|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Shifnal]], [[Shropshire]] | death_date = | death_place = | school_tradition = [[Analytic philosophy]] | main_interests = [[Philosophy of language]], [[philosophy of mind]], [[ontology]], [[emotions]], [[logic]] | influences = [[Bernard Bolzano|Bolzano]], [[Ludwig Wittgenstein|Wittgenstein]] | influenced = | notable_ideas = }} '''Kevin Mulligan''' (born 23 June 1951) is a [[British people|British]] [[philosopher]], working on [[ontology]], the [[philosophy of mind]], and [[Austrian philosophy]]. He is currently Honorary Professor at the [[University of Geneva]], Full Professor at the [[Università della Svizzera italiana]], Director of Research at the Institute of Philosophy of Lugano, member of the [[Academia Europaea]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ae-info.org/ae/Member/Mulligan_Kevin|title=Academy of Europe: Mulligan Kevin|last=Hoffmann|first=Ilire Hasani, Robert|website=www.ae-info.org|access-date=2017-03-30}}</ref> and of the [[Royal Swedish Academy of Letters, History and Antiquities|Royal Swedish Academy of Letters]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vitterhetsakad.se/ledamoter/utlandska_ledamoter|title=Kungliga Vitterhetsakademien - Ledamöter - Utländska ledamöter|website=www.vitterhetsakad.se|access-date=2017-03-30}}</ref> He is also known for his work with [[Peter Simons (academic)|Peter Simons]] and [[Barry Smith (academic and ontologist)|Barry Smith]] on [[metaphysics]], [[Austrian philosophy|Austrian]] and [[Polish philosophy]].
