'''''Moralium dogma philosophorum''''' ("Teaching of the philosophers on moral questions") is a [[Latin language|Latin]] work of the 12th century. Its authorship is uncertain: it has been attributed to [[William of Conches]], to [[Walter of Châtillon]] and (less likely) to [[Alan of Lille]]. Parallels exist between this work, the anonymous ''[[Ysagoge in theologiam]]'' (written between 1141 and 1157), and the text ''De virtutibus et vitiis'' by Alan of Lille (written between 1155 and 1165).

